@startuml
title Context - Authority Boundaries (Definition vs Runtime vs Output)
left to right direction
hide empty members

package "Definition Authority" {
  class TypedScriptDefinitions {
    +script_file_type_contracts
    +ctx_profiles
    +capability_usage_contracts
  }
}

package "Runtime Authority" {
  class CanonicalRuntimeState {
    +metrics_state
    +phenomena_state
    +scale_state
  }

  class DerivedRuntimeState {
    +transient_indices
    +realization_caches
    +work queues
  }
}

package "Output Application" {
  class CapabilityOutputState {
    +render_runtime
    +physics_runtime
    +audio_runtime
    +service_runtime
  }
}

TypedScriptDefinitions -[#1E88E5]-> CanonicalRuntimeState : defines admissible mutation contracts in Canonical Runtime Authority
TypedScriptDefinitions -[#1E88E5]-> DerivedRuntimeState : defines rebuild policies in Derived Runtime Authority
CanonicalRuntimeState -[#43A047]-> DerivedRuntimeState : derives transient structures in Derived Runtime Authority
DerivedRuntimeState -[#43A047]-> CapabilityOutputState : drives output intents via Output Application
CapabilityOutputState -[#8E24AA]-> DerivedRuntimeState : emits runtime telemetry back to Derived Runtime Authority
@enduml
